==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snotter
<hw>Snot"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Snot</er>.]</ety> <def>To snivel; to cry or whine.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Grose.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snotter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Snotter
<hw>Snot"ter</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol. uncertain.]</ety>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A rope going over a yardarm, used to bend a
tripping line to, in sending down topgallant and royal yards in vessels
of war; also, the short line supporting the heel of the sprit in a small
boat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snottery</ent>⟦br⟧
